     /    \  __/      DarkWind's Guide to new adventurers         \__
    /      \/         -----------------------------------             \
   / For those players just starting out here at DarkWind, I High Sage \
  /  Segovia, Master of the great Library of Telthar have taken it      \
  \ upon myself to write this piece of parchment in the hopes of making  \
  / life for the new adventurer an easier task.  Below is inscribed the   \
  \ little bit of knowledge I have gained from my years talking with      /
  / other adventurers.  Some were successful in their ways, others were   \
  \ not so lucky, but I feel that I was able to learn from both their     /
  / successes as well as their failures.  If you feel that what I may     \
  | have to say could be of value to you, please read on...               /
  |                                                                      /
 /  First and foremost:  When you first log on, where should you go,    <
/   and what should you do?  A few places you must know as a new player  \
\   are the Adventurer's guild, Erga's newbie supplies, Grondor's Inn     \
/   and Taylor's shop.                                                     >
|                                                                         /
/   Adventurer's Guild: From this starting point (the 4 way intersection /
\   with a map of DarkWind), go 1 west then 1 south and you will get to /
/   the adventurers guild.  The Newbies' Tome of adventuring located   /
\   there contains a lot more information about Darkwind.   It also   /
/   describes some of our rules and regulations.  Also inside the     \
\   guild, but 2 east of the Tome, you will end up in the party        \_
|   registry room.  A party is a group of adventurers who choose to      |
|   explore DarkWind together.  Only the person who will be the party    \
|   leader needs to go to this room to 'register'.  DarkWind is          /
/   oriented towards partying and while it is possible to adventure      \_
\   alone and be successful, people who party with others are very        /
/   likely to do much better.  (Especially at lower levels!)             /
\                                                                     __/
/   Erga's Newbie equipment shop: From the starting point, go 3 west  \
\   then 1 south.  Type 'arm' to get yourself some free equipment.     \
/   Don't forget to 'wear' your armour and 'wield' your sword!!        /
\                                                                     /
/   After level 2 you cannot use Erga's equipment shop, but you will /
\   find a donated equipment room 5 north, one east from the center /
 \  of town.  Return items here for other players to use, when you /
 /  are done with them, or decide not to sell weapons and armour  /
/   you discover in your adventures.                             /_____
\                                                                     /_
 \  Grondor's Inn: is a place reserved for newer players where they     \
 /  can find food and drink. Most of the other Inns and Pubs in town    /
 \  cater more to the higher level adventurer, so this is a good place  \
 /  to find food and drink to help you heal after some hard adventuring. |
 |                                                                      /
 \ Taylor's Shop: After a hard day adventuring, it's only natural that  \
  \ you would want to take all your spoils back to town and get some     /
  / cold hard cash for them.  Making a trip to Taylor's Shop is just the \
 /  place you want to go.  From the starting point, go 4 west, 2 south   /
/   then 1 west and you'll be there.  If you have a few extra coins in   \
\   your pocket, you can also go here and buy from a fair sized list.    /
 \                                                                      /
  \ Temple of Mitra: As always seems the case with adventuring, death   \
/\/ sometimes seems inevitable.  In the unfortunate case where you find  \
\   yourself no longer among the living, head to the Temple of Mitra and /
/   'pray' to the gods and they will return your body to you.  Be        \
\   warned though.  Dying takes a lot out of a persons soul, so when you /
/   return to the land of the living, you may not be as hearty as before \
\   you died.  To get to the Temple from the starting point, go 4 west,  /
/   then 1 north.                                                        \
\                                                                        /
/   Ok, you now have the town down rather well, and want to head out in  \
\   search of adventure.  There are several places a new adventurer      /
/   can go and expect a good chance of success.                          \
\                                                                         \
/   The TOWN GRAVEYARD, it can be found just outside of the west gate of   \____
\/\ the city.  To get there from the center of town go west, to the west gate  /
   > 'exit', go west thrice more and then south.                              /
  /                                                                          /
 /   A FARMYARD of chickens, piglets, cows is located to the west of town   /
 \   as well go: 5 west, 'exit', 4 west, 3 north, 2 east, then north.      /
 /   None of the creatures here are aggressive (attacking you before you  /
/    attack them), so it's a fairly easy place to start.                  \
|                                                                          \
\  En route to the FARMYARD you will pass a black void,  'enter' the void  /
 \ and read the sign for information on that newbie area.                 /
 /                                                                       /
/  The BEACH northeast of town will tempt your adventurous spirit.      /
\  From the starting point, go 6 north, 'exit', and then 6 east.        \/\
/  It becomes more difficult as you continue to the north.                /
\                                                                        /
 \ A NEWBIE MENAGERIE of small animals is also north of town.  Proceed  /
 / north of the starting point, 'exit', and then 3 north, then east.    \
 \                                                                      /
  \  A FOREST full of woodland creatures lies along the river          /
   \  southwest of Darkwind.  It contains a variety of non-aggressive /  /\
    |  creatures to challenge any striving adventurer.  From the       \/ /
   /  starting point, the forest is located 5 west, then exit, w, and    /
  /  finally go 6 south.  The path to the southwest enters the forest.  <
 |                                                                       \
/   The MERCENARY town south of town.  From the starting point, go        \/\
\   5 south, 'exit', 5 south again, then east. This area gets harder       _/
/   as you penetrate further east and south.                              /
\                                                                        /
/   TILLMAN's village fields and playground.  From the starting point    \
\   it's 5 west, 'exit', 4 west, 2 north, 1 west, 1 south, 1 west,       /
/   then 'enter'.                                                       /
\                                                                      /
 \  Another area allows you to terrorize gnomes.  They live out of     \
  \ town to the west.  Go towards Tillman's village, but go 5 west     /
  / instead of 4.  A troll lives at the intersection, but he won't    +
 /  harm you if you don't bother him.  Go south from the intersection  \
/   but beware.  Some gnomes have very nasty tempers.                  |
\                                                                       \
 \  The home of Ezekiel, renowned sage of DarkWind, is also a fitting    \
  \ place for aspiring adventurers to explore.  This is an excellent     /
  | area to learn the basics of questing, as the sage will surely have   |
 /  an errand or two for you to do.  His place can be found by traveling /
/   out the north gate of the city, then heading 8 north, 3 west, and   /
|   2 more north.                                                      /
\                                                                      \_
/   The last low level area is the old graveyard behind the Temple of    \
\   Mitra.  They usually don't like people back there though because of  /
/   the problems they have been having lately with the dear departed not \
\   staying in the graves where they belong, so they keep the door locked \
/   But sources tell me that a spare key can usually be found in the    __/
\   attic of the temple.  To get there, follow the directions to the   /
 |  Temple.                                                           /
 \                                                                    \
  \ The Parchment and Package service: If you need to get a hold of a  \__
  / comrade but they dont seem to be around at the moment, you can always \
  \ head over to the Parchment and Package service and send them some     /
   \mail.  When they next come around, they will be informed of your      \
  _/message and they can then read it at their leisure.                   /
_/                                                                       /
\   You have received a small invisible gift, which is yours to use     /
/   as you desire, and to customize as to your needs.  It is an alias   \/\
\   tracker.  It will let you store frequently used commands in a simple  /
 \  format.  Several aliases are already built into DarkWind, such as,   /
 /  n for north, s for south, ne for northeast, and so on, but you might \
/   add your own to your alias 'look at' as an alias use                 /
\   'alias la look at', which will add 'la' to your alias list.  Review /
/   your aliases with the 'alias list' command                         /____
\                                                                          /
/   There are some terms you might need to understand as you explore      /
\/\ DarkWinds many areas.                                                /
  / New adventurers are referred to endearingly as NEWBIES.  All NEWBIES \
 /  can talk to each other no matter where they are in DarkWind using the \
/   NEWBIE channel.  'newbie message text' will display the message to    /
\   others listening to the channel.  It will look like:                 /
 \       [Newbie] Segovia: Hi fellow Newbies                            /
  / If you get tired of the NEWBIE messages, 'tune newbie off', will   /
 /  turn off the messages.   'tune newbie on' will let you once again  \
 \   listen and speak to your fellow newbies.                           \
  |                                                                      |
  | Your starting area is often refered to as COT(Center of Town),  it   |
  | is the crossroads where the DarkWind map and the dispenser of this   /
  / scroll are located.                                                 /
 /                                                                      |
 |                 A FEW OTHER HINTS and SUGGESTIONS                   /
 \                                                                    /
 / As you explore DarkWind's many areas, you will encounter animals,  \_/\
|   humans, and other monsters to kill, but which will also inflict      /
|   damage on you, in proportion to their strength.  One quick way to    \
/  recover is to enter an ajoining room and 'sit' down.  Other healing is/
\  available through eating foods, or drinking alcohol which can        /
 \ be purchased in various inns and pubs in town.  When you visit      /
 / an inn/pub also grab a corpse burner, which will allow you to      /
/  burn your kills.  You can sell the ashes produced to inn/pubs      \_/\
\  increasing your cash on hand.  To sell the ash go to an inn or pub    /
 \ and 'process ash'.  The ashes are used to produce food and alcohol   /
 /  which you can purchase.  When you 'eat food', or 'drink alcohol'   /
<  you will heal faster than by just sitting.                         /
 \                                                                   /
 | RL is an abbreviation for something called Real Life, which is a   \
 / state of confusion where people are not living within the realms   /
/  of reality provided by DarkWind.                                  /
\                                                                    \
 \  Other technical terms that don't fit this version of reality, but \
 /    used frequently are:                                            /
 |    AFK - Away from keyboard                                       /
/     LD - Link dead, disconnected from DarkWind by unknown powers   \/\
|                                                                       \
\   Well for the time, that's all the knowledge I have to offer.         /
 \  If I think of more I shall add to this scroll and divulge that      /
  \  additional wisdom to you.                                         /
   \                                                                  /
    \  I know this parchment may seem insignificant when you look    /
     \  at the tremendous task before you, but at the very least    /
